s, La Cr\xc3\xa8che 2011.</li>\n<li>(fr) Nadia Salmi: <i>Des \xc3\xa9toiles sombres dans le ciel.</i> OH \xc3\x89ditions, Paris 2011.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="War_children_in_Norway">War children in Norway</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=War_children&amp;action=edit&amp;section=54" title="Edit section: War children in Norway">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><cite id="CITEREFOlsen2002" class="citation">Olsen, Kare (2002), <i>Vater: Deutscher. - Das Schicksal der norwegischen Lebensbornkinder und ihrer M\xc3\xbctter von 1940 bis heute</i> [<i>Father: German</i>] (in German)</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWar+children&amp;rft.aufirst=Kare&amp;rft.aulast=Olsen&amp;rft.btitle=Vater%3A+Deutscher.+-+Das+Schicksal+der+norwegischen+Lebensbornkinder+und+ihrer+M%C3%BCtter+von+1940+bis+heute&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> (the authoritative resource on Lebensborn in Norway and available in Norwegian).</li>\n<li><cite class="citation"><i>Krigens barn: De norske krigsbarna og deres m\xc3\xb8dre</i> (in Norwegian), Aschehoug, 1998, <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/82-03-29090-6" title="Special:BookSources/82-03-29090-6">82-03-29090-6</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWar+children&amp;rft.btitle=Krigens+barn%3A+De+norske+krigsbarna+og+deres+m%C3%B8dre&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.isbn=82-03-29090-6&amp;rft.place=Aschehoug&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</li>\n<li>Eystein Eggen, <i>The Boy from Gimle</i>, 1993.</li>\n<li><cite id="CITEREFEggen1993" class="citation">Eggen, Eystein (1993), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://home.online.no/~kluwer/gimlefr.htm"><i>L\xe2\x80\x99enfant de Gimle</i></a> [<i>The Boy from Gimle</i>] (in French)</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWar+children&amp;rft.aufirst=Eystein&amp;rft.aulast=Eggen&amp;rft.btitle=L%E2%80%99enfant+de+Gimle&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fhome.online.no%2F~kluwer%2Fgimlefr.htm&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</li>\n<li><cite id="CITEREFSimonsen2006" class="citation">Simonsen, Eva (2006), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://edoc.hu-berlin.de/nordeuropaforum/2006-2/simonsen-eva-25/PDF/simonsen.pdf"><i>Into the open \xe2\x80\x93 or hidden away? The construction of war children as a social category in post-war Norway and Germany</i></a> <span style="font-size:85%;">(PDF)</span>, <b>2</b>, NordEuropaforum, pp.&#160;25\xe2\x80\x9349</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWar+children&amp;rft.aufirst=Eva&amp;rft.aulast=Simonsen&amp;rft.btitle=Into+the+open+%E2%80%93+or+hidden+away%3F++The+construction+of+war+children+as+a+social+category+in+post-war+Norway+and+Germany&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.pages=25-49&amp;rft.pub=NordEuropaforum&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fedoc.hu-berlin.de%2Fnordeuropaforum%2F2006-2%2Fsimonsen-eva-25%2FPDF%2Fsimonsen.pdf&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</li>\n<li>(no) <i>Borgersrud, L.:</i> Staten og krigsbarna: en historisk unders\xc3\xb8kelse av statsmyndighetenes behandling av krigsbarna i de f\xc3\xb8rste etterkrigs\xc3\xa5rene, 2004</li>\n<li>(no) <i>Ellingsen, D.:</i> Krigsbarns levek\xc3\xa5r: en registerbasert unders\xc3\xb8kelse, 2004</li>\n<li>(no) <i>Borgersrud, L.:</i> Vi ville ikke ha dem: Statens behandling av de norske krigsbarna, 2005</li>\n<li>(no) <i>Ericsson, K. &amp; E. Simonsen:</i> Krigsbarn i fredstid, 2005</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Representation_in_film">Representation in film</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=War_children&amp;action=edit&amp;section=55" title="Edit section: Representation in film">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><cite id="CITEREFFreitagD.C3.B6bber2007" class="citation">Freitag, Susanne; D\xc3\xb6bber, Claudia (2007), <i>Feindeskind. Mein Vater war ein deutscher Soldat</i> [<i>Enemies\' child. My father was a German soldier</i>] (in German), Paris: ZDF-Studios</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWar+children&amp;rft.au=D%C3%B6bber%2C+Claudia&amp;rft.aufirst=Susanne&amp;rft.aulast=Freitag&amp;rft.btitle=Feindeskind.+Mein+Vater+war+ein+deutscher+Soldat&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.place=Paris&amp;rft.pub=ZDF-Studios&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>. Shown by German TV: Phoenix on January 2, 2010, 14h\xe2\x80\x9314h45. (Wehrmachtsauskunftsstelle Berlin, discrimination of mothers and children, French association of war children ANEG, family reunion of siblings with common German father, with corresponding French mother or corresponding German mother).<sup id="cite_ref-ReferenceA_59-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ReferenceA-59">[59]</a></sup></li>\n<li><cite class="citation"><i>betrifft. Besatzungskinder</i> [<i>Ref.: War children</i>] (in German)</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWar+children&amp;rft.btitle=betrifft.+Besatzungskinder&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>. Shown by regional German TV SWR/SR on December 2, 2009, 20h15\xe2\x80\x9321h. Meeting of German-French children stemming from a German soldier stationed in France, or vice versa from a French father stationed in Germany, search for their fathers. Interview with the president of French association of war children ANEG.<sup id="cite_ref-ReferenceA_59-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ReferenceA-59">[59]</a></sup></li>\n<li><i>A Woman in Berlin</i> (2010), drama based on an anonymous journal, about German women struggling to survive during the Russian invasion and occupation</li>\n<li><i>Two Lives</i> (2012), German drama film written and directed by Georg Maas about adult war children being recruited as <a href="/wiki/Stasi" title="Stasi">Stasi</a> agents and sent to Norway to be reunited with their "birth" mothers by claiming places of children who were sent away for adoption. Starring <a href="/wiki/Juliane_Kohler" class="mw-redirect" title="Juliane Kohler">Juliane Kohler</a> and <a href="/wiki/Liv_Ullman" class="mw-redirect" title="Liv Ullman">Liv Ullman</a> and the official German entry in the 2013 Academy Awards, it is based on a novel by Hannelore Hippe.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="References">References</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=War_children&amp;action=edit&amp;section=56" title="Edit section: References">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<ol class="references">\n<li id="cite_note-drolshaben9-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-drolshaben9_1-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFDrolshagen2005" class="citation">Drolshagen, Ebba D (2005), <i>Wehrmachtskinder. Auf der Suche nach dem nie gekannten Vater</i> [<i>Children of German soldiers. Searching for the unknown father</i>] (in German), M\xc3\xbcnchen: Droemer, p.&#160;9</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rf